        <div class='col-sm-6'>
            <h3>Grading</h3>
            <p class='bigger'>Breakdown:</p>

            <ul>
                <li><strong>40%</strong> &mdash; 1 Project</li>
                <li><strong>50%</strong> &mdash; 10 Exercises <em>(5pts each)</em></li>
                <li><strong>10%</strong> &mdash; In-Class Exercises and Lecture</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Grade Change Policies</h4>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    I will not increase a grade for any assignment, lab, or test
                    unless you present me with unambiguous evidence proving that
                    there was a mistake in the instructions/question or in the
                    grading process.  You may only request a grade change outside
                    of class.
                </li>
                <li>
                    I do not grade on a curve, but I will evaluate grading issues
                    on a case-by-case basis if the majority of the class (80% or
                    more) is not able to successfully complete an assignment or
                    answer a question on a test correctly.  If I choose to
                    retroactively change the score for a question or assignment, I
                    will do so for the entire class and inform students of the
                    reason.
                </li>
            </ul>
