    {# ROW #}
    <div class='row'>
        <div class='col-sm-6'>
            <h3>Attendance Policy</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    Attendance is mandatory on the first day of class, per 
                    <a href='http://registrar.fsu.edu/bulletin/undergrad/info/acad_regs.htm' title='Here is the Policy'>FSU policy</a>.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Attendance is mandatory at all in-class activities in
                    order to receive full credit.  There is no make-up for
                    activities.  Refer to the course calendar for activity
                    session dates.
                </li>

                <li>
                    There is no formal attendance policy for lecture sessions,
                    but I will take attendance at all course meetings.  Lecture is
                    <strong>the salient component</strong> in this course.  Miss
                    class at your own discretion.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class='col-sm-6'>
            <h3>Assignment Submission Policy</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    I will be assigning several exercises that you are to
                    complete and submit by the following week via the Blackboard
                    Course Website.  We will discuss homework assignments during
                    lecture sessions. They are due by midnight on the following
                    Tuesday.
                </li>

                <li>
                    You must contact me personally to turn in a late
                    assignment.  I will deduct 10% of the assignment’s value
                    for each day the assignment is late.  I will not accept
                    assignments more than 5 days late.  Thus, it is important
                    for you to manage your time in such a way as to ensure
                    that you complete assignments on time.
                </li>

                <li>
                    I will not assign any homework other than that which is
                    already listed in the course calendar without notifying
                    students ahead of time.
                </li>

                <li>
                    It is your responsibility to read the submission
                    instructions, located on the course website, for all
                    homework assignments.  You must comply with all of the
                    requirements listed in the submission instructions.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Technical issues or computer errors are not acceptable
                    excuses for late or missing assignment submissions. The
                    College provides computer labs to students who need them.
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    You should plan to work outside of class for three to nine
                    hours a week at the start of the semester, and six to
                    twelve hours per week at the end of the semester.
                </li>
            </ul>            
        </div>
    </div>

